<p>None; it’s just syntactic sugar.  It does the same thing under the hood.</p>
<p>Modern command-based has a <em>lot</em> of syntactic sugaring like this, because without it Java rapidly gets very verbose.</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":29,"updated_at":"2023-09-25T15:56:04.299Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":159,"readers_count":158,"score":46.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":441336,"topic_slug":"programming-triggers-for-joystick-switches","display_username":"Eli Barnett","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":12381,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Robot apartments! invisible suburbs! skeleton treasuries!"},"post_url":"/t/programming-triggers-for-joystick-switches/441336/6","custom_user_title":"Robot apartments! invisible suburbs! skeleton treasuries!","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3237470,"name":"","username":"robojack","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/49beb7/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-10-04T15:21:19.057Z","cooked":"<p>I guess I’m still lost.  If I use CommandGenericHID,I would create a controller with</p>
<p>private final CommandGenericHID  m_controller = new CommandGenericHID(prot:0);</p>
<p>What is the syntax for declaring a Trigger using  button 1 on the CommandGenericHID controller.</p>
<p>I assume something like</p>
<p>private final Trigger B1    but I get lost on how to link a button to m_controller</p>
<p>I’m sure I’m missing something obvious but if someone could give the complete set of statements to set up a trigger like this, Id appreciate it</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":29,"updated_at":"2023-10-04T15:21:19.057Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":138,"readers_count":137,"score":32.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":441336,"topic_slug":"programming-triggers-for-joystick-switches","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":60576,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/programming-triggers-for-joystick-switches/441336/7","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3237476,"name":"Eli Barnett","username":"Oblarg","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/oblarg/{size}/161674_2.png","created_at":"2023-10-04T15:35:52.061Z","cooked":"<p><code>CommandGenericHID</code> has methods that return the <code>Trigger</code> instances - you do not need to declare the trigger yourself, nor store the trigger locally in a field (so, you can do away with the <code>private final Trigger</code> entirely).</p>
<p>You can use <code>CommandGenericHID</code> to do trigger bindings entirely inline without ever using the <code>new</code> keyword - this saves a lot of visual clutter.  The functionality is exactly the same as if you had constructed <code>Triggers</code> manually.</p>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":29,"updated_at":"2023-10-04T15:36:29.110Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":7,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":134,"readers_count":133,"score":31.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":441336,"topic_slug":"programming-triggers-for-joystick-switches","display_username":"Eli Barnett","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":60576,"username":"robojack","name":"","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/49beb7/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":12381,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Robot apartments! invisible suburbs! skeleton treasuries!"},"post_url":"/t/programming-triggers-for-joystick-switches/441336/8","custom_user_title":"Robot apartments! invisible suburbs! skeleton treasuries!","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3238632,"name":"","username":"robojack","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/49beb7/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-10-08T18:11:48.090Z","cooked":"<p>I guess I’m still lost.  I’d like an example of running a command based on a trigger for one of the buttons on a GenericHID device.  Or an example of the same thing for a Joystick or Xbox.  Sorry to be such a newbie but Java and I (maybe just I ) need a translator.</p>
<p>Thanks</p>","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"posts_count":29,"updated_at":"2023-10-08T18:11:48.090Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":8,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":126,"readers_count":125,"score":30.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":441336,"topic_slug":"programming-triggers-for-joystick-switches","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":12381,"username":"Oblarg","name":"Eli Barnett","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/oblarg/{size}/161674_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":60576,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/programming-triggers-for-joystick-switches/441336/9","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3238659,"name":"","username":"SammyPants","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/sammypants/{size}/188763_2.png","created_at":"2023-10-08T23:16:44.076Z","cooked":"<p>ok so do what your asking assuming a CommandGenericHID you could do</p>
<pre><code class="lang-java">CommandGenericHID m_controller = new CommandGenericHID(0);
m_controller.x().ontrue(soAndSoCommand);
</code></pre>
